            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong>, the <strong>lime leaf[ves] </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving – this is your <strong>fragrant rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
